text.tspan: optionally add instant glue in the corners
Mechanical interface is glued to the FlexFill
backing, flex PCB is tied to FlexFill backing
PETG backing is 3D printed face-up so that
the PCB slot has no defects due to supports
When printing with FlexFill, supports should be
avoided at all costs. Hence, the FlexFill backing is
printed face-down, and no PCB slot is provided. To
minimise printing time and as such minimise potential
failure, the mechanical interface to the Robotiq
gripper is printed separately in PLA.
